U.S. Stocks Rebound as Oil’s Plunge Drives Up Consumer Companies, FedEx

-- B y   N i c k   B a k e r
-- 
2011-05-05T16:07:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/u-s-stocks-rebound-as-oil-s-plunge-drives-up-consumer-companies-fedex.html
U.S. stocks rebounded, erasing a
fourth straight decline in the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index, as
falling oil prices spurred gains in consumer companies, airlines
and  FedEx Corp. (FDX)   The S&P 500 rose less than 0.1 percent to 1,347.44 at 12:04
p.m.  New York  time after falling as much as 0.8 percent. Oil
plunged 5.7 percent to $103 a barrel in New York.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at 
 nbaker7@bloomberg.net  